==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Feculence
<hw>Fec"u*lence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>faeculentia</ets> dregs, filth: cf. F.
<ets>f⟦eacute⟧culence</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state or
quality of being feculent; muddiness; foulness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is feculent; sediment; lees;
dregs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Feculency</ent>⟦br⟧
